&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;blockquote&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&amp;lt;BEGIN LOG&amp;gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Cole:&lt;/strong&gt; Hi, fifty-fifty-seven. How are you feeling?&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;SCP-5057:&lt;/strong&gt; The same.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Cole:&lt;/strong&gt; I&#039;m sorry you&#039;re not feeling well, but I&#039;d like to talk to you about what happened.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;SCP-5057:&lt;/strong&gt; Okay.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Cole:&lt;/strong&gt; Researcher Rex, how did he treat you?&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;SCP-5057:&lt;/strong&gt; Rex was friend. Yeah. Good friend.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Cole:&lt;/strong&gt; Then why did you do that to the portrait of you two?&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;[Dr. Cole points to the portrait of Researcher Rex and SCP-5057.]&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;SCP-5057:&lt;/strong&gt; I am not wanting to talk about it.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Cole:&lt;/strong&gt; Was he cruel to you?&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;SCP-5057:&lt;/strong&gt; What is cruel?&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Cole:&lt;/strong&gt; Hmm. Being cruel is like being really mean and unfriendly to someone.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;[There is a ten-second silence.]&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;SCP-5057:&lt;/strong&gt; Yes. He was of being cruel.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Cole:&lt;/strong&gt; What did he do?&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;SCP-5057:&lt;/strong&gt; He made me feel toxic.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Cole:&lt;/strong&gt; I see. For what it&#039;s worth, I don&#039;t think you&#039;re toxic to talk to, fify-fifty-seven.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;SCP-5057:&lt;/strong&gt; Really?&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Cole:&lt;/strong&gt; Yeah. You seem like an alright person who was mistreated and lead to believe something that isn&#039;t true.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;SCP-5057:&lt;/strong&gt; But I am still toxic.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Cole:&lt;/strong&gt; You may be toxic to eat, but you are not a toxic person. If anything, I believe Researcher Rex is the real toxic person here.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;SCP-5057:&lt;/strong&gt; I am&amp;#8230; not toxic?&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Cole:&lt;/strong&gt; No. You&#039;re you. And that&#039;s perfectly fine. You know, a real friend wouldn&#039;t make you feel toxic. A real friend cares about what you have to say and actually listens to you.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;SCP-5057:&lt;/strong&gt; I am me&amp;#8230; I am not knowing of what to say.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Cole:&lt;/strong&gt; You don&#039;t need to say anything. Why don&#039;t you go ahead and paint something new? I have to get in contact with someone about something.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;SCP-5057:&lt;/strong&gt; Okay!&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&amp;lt;END LOG&amp;gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/blockquote&gt;
